    {
      "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nRussia will stay in ISS program at least until 2028: report\n\n\nBy\n\nMike Wall \n\npublished 44 minutes ago\n\n\n\nRussia's departure from the International Space Station program isn't exactly imminent, it would seem.\n\n\n\n",
      "url": "https://www.space.com/russia-stay-international-space-station-2028"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nUS Postal Service to launch James Webb Space Telescope 'forever' stamp\n\n\nBy\n\nBrett Tingley \n\npublished about 1 hour ago\n\n\n\nThe stamp commemorates the start of the telescope's science mission and depicts the telescope's iconic golden honeycomb mirror and its large sunshields in space.\n\n\n\n",
      "url": "https://www.space.com/james-webb-space-telescope-forever-stamps-us-postal-service"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n'Castaway' gamma-ray bursts come from distant early galaxies\n\n\nBy\n\nRobert Lea \n\npublished about 2 hours ago\n\n\n\nIntense blasts of radiation called gamma-ray bursts originate from neutron star mergers in distant galaxies, but until now the origins of some of these eruptions couldn't be pinpointed.\n\n\n\n",
      "url": "https://www.space.com/gamma-ray-bursts-distant-galaxies"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nExperimental Zephyr drone sets new record for uncrewed flight duration\n\n\nBy\n\nBrett Tingley \n\npublished about 3 hours ago\n\n\n\nThe experimental Airbus Zephyr drone has been airborne for over 42 straight days, setting a new record for an uncrewed flight.\n\n\n\n",
      "url": "https://www.space.com/airbus-zephyr-drone-long-endurance-flight-record"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nChina steers cargo spacecraft to fiery death in Earth's atmosphere\n\n\nBy\n\nMike Wall \n\npublished about 4 hours ago\n\n\n\nChina guided its Tianzhou 3 cargo spacecraft to a fiery death in Earth's atmosphere late Tuesday night (July 26).\n\n\n\n",
      "url": "https://www.space.com/china-tianzhou-3-cargo-spacecraft-reenters-atmosphere"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe north pole of Jupiter has mesmerizing storms, new Juno images reveal\n\n\nBy\n\nTereza Pultarova \n\npublished about 4 hours ago\n\n\n\nPowerful storms around the North Pole of Jupiter swirl in mesmerizing images captured by NASA's Juno probe during its close approach to the giant planet on July 5.\n\n\n\n",
      "url": "https://www.space.com/jupiter-mesmerizing-storms-north-pole-juno-images"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMars sample return mission adds 2 helicopters, scraps 'fetch' rover\nThe NASA-European mission campaign has been revamped again.\n\n\n",
      "url": "https://www.space.com/ingenuity-class-helicopters-mars-sample-return"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBrilliant fireball explodes high in Texas sky before dawn (video)\nNo word yet on whether there were meteorites after a small space body broke up harmlessly Sunday (July 24), high in Earth's atmosphere.\n\n\n",
      "url": "https://www.space.com/texas-fireball-high-sky-hundreds-people"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe north pole of Jupiter has mesmerizing storms, new Juno images reveal\nScientists are trying to figure out what gives those storms their color and shape.\n\n\n",
      "url": "https://www.space.com/jupiter-mesmerizing-storms-north-pole-juno-images"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n25-ton Chinese rocket debris will fall to Earth around July 31, experts predict\nIt's too soon to tell where the 25-ton piece of space junk will come down.\n\n\n",
      "url": "https://www.space.com/chinese-rocket-space-debris-fall-july-31"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe James Webb Space Telescope is on the hunt for the universe's 1st-ever supermassive black holes\n\n\n\n",
      "url": "https://www.space.com/james-webb-space-telescope-first-supermassive-black-holes"
    },
    {
      "text": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHow seriously should we take Russia's latest threat to leave the ISS?\nRussia still left itself room to stay in the ISS program after 2024 if the country intends to do so, experts say.\n\n\n",
      "url": "https://www.space.com/russia-space-station-departure-threat-seriousness"
    },
    {
